Model & Code

Hybrid Forecasting Model Architecture

Model Components

  • Meta Prophet: Time series decomposition for seasonality, trends, and holidays
  • XGBoost: Gradient boosting for complex feature interactions and weekday effects
  • Ensemble Blending: Weighted combination of both model outputs
  • Automated Pipeline: End-to-end processing from data ingestion to forecast generation

Why This Hybrid Approach?

Traditional time series models struggle with FMCG demand patterns due to:

  • Promotional spikes that don't follow seasonal patterns
  • Weekday vs weekend buying behavior variations
  • Competitor activities affecting demand
  • Multiple external factors beyond historical patterns

The Prophet + XGBoost hybrid captures both temporal patterns (Prophet) and feature-based patterns (XGBoost), delivering superior accuracy for FMCG forecasting.
